  %li
    Why use NumPy?
    %ul
      %li I can use NumPy to do many types of linear algebra calculations:
      %li
        %pre
          %code
            import numpy as np
            array1_a = np.array([1.1,2.2,3.39])      
            array2_a = np.array([1.1, 3.2, 2.39])
            \# Transpose:
            array1_a.shape = (1,3)
            array3_a = array1_a.T
            print(array3_a)
            \# Matrix multiplication:
            mult1_a = np.matmul(array1_a,array3_a) # rows x columns
            \# Inverse:
            m1_a = np.array([[1.1,2.2,3.39],[1.1, 3.2, 2.39]])
            print(m1_a)
            inv_a = np.linalg.pinv(m1_a)
            print(inv_a)
            \# Identity Matrix:
            id_a = np.matmul(m1_a,inv_a)
            print(id_a)
      %li I should know NumPy if I want to use popular Python machine learning modules.
      %li
        %hr/


